-- Southern China Should Prepare for Heavy Rains Today, Weather Agency Warns
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-26T00:53:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-26/southern-china-should-prepare-for-heavy-rains-today-weather-agency-warns.html

          
          
             Southern China should prepare for
torrential rain today and early tomorrow,  the China
Meteorological Administration  warned this morning.  
 Provinces including southern Zhejiang, Jiangxi, most of
Fujian, Guangdong and central to southern Guangxi will receive
heavy or torrential rain today, the agency said, urging local
governments to prepare for disasters such as landslide.  
 -- Feiwen Rong . Editor: Jim McDonald  
